What you need to know:  Saturday stages are divided into four:131.82km-long Tempio Pausania (12.03 km) and Erula-Tula (15.27 km) in the morning followed by Coiluna - Loelle (21.60 km) and Monte Lerno (17.01 km) stages in the afternoon.On Sunday, a new champion will be known after the Cala Flumini (12.55km) and Sassari-Argentiera (7.10km) tests, ran twice followed by the Wolf Power Stage.Championship leader Kalle Rovanpera hopes to extend his three-rallies winning streak.